-- Hostess Adviser Says Customers Interested in Buying Brands
-- B y   D a w n   M c C a r t y   a n d   P h i l   M i l f o r d
-- 2012-11-21T17:43:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/hostess-adviser-says-customers-interested-in-buying-brands.html
Hostess Brands Inc. customers are
interested in buying the company’s brands and the baker of
Twinkies and Wonder bread may generate about $1 billion from
asset sales, a financial adviser said in court. The company has
been “undervalued” for years and there is “very intense”
comeptition for its brands, Joshua Scherer of Perella Weinberg
Partners LP said today at a hearing in U.S.  Bankruptcy Court  in
 White Plains , New York. Hostess isn’t administratively
insolvent, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dawn McCarty in Wilmington at 
 dmccarty@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
